<br>
I'll try to get inside their heads a bit.<br>
<br>
One is acceptable, because it's there to make sacrifices, to accept other people's definition of good (you know, the dark elf necromancer that is &quot;good&quot;, blah de blah blah.)<br>
<br>
However, any more than one evil in the group and they can start to gain a foothold, can start to collaborate and preach.  Trust me, Antoin does. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
So therefore one is okay for flexibility.  More and you're going to be influenced and the group will be jerked around by the evils, because, well, evils do that.<br>
<br>
(And some evils do, and delight in it.  Some don't.  Some don't care.)<br>
<br>
Crusaders of Thunder does not allow grouping with ANY Shadowknight (they lovingly call us &quot;Anti-paladins,&quot; a name I so endear that I will brand it on every single one of their foreheads...sorry, that was IC) or Necromancer, and they're adamant about it:  <br>
<br>
I had to arbite a little situation, went to see how the investigation was going (all IC of course) and was basically shown the door.  I didn't mind.  It's what I expected.<br>
<br>
Oh yeah.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>And the kid was what, 23, going on 24?  By the original definition that roleplay starts after 20, he was already roleplaying.  HELLO!</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
