<br>
I agree with everything you said...in fact, I go out of my way to think of creative RP that will allow me to aid evils at times.<br>
<br>
Example:  A troll asks me for a SoW...I cast it on him and emote that I hope that the extra speed causes him to trip over his own feet and break his neck.<br>
<br>
A DE asks me for a port to Wakening Lands, I might give it while emoting that I hope Wuoshi is awake and wants to have her for breakfast (while sending a tell to ensure that the person has good faction with CoV...I wouldn't be able to forgive myself for porting someone to their death).<br>
<br>
Other times, I might simply say &quot;Nay, I donna help yer kind&quot; to a request, depending on which of my good aligned friends are around.  In Saga, the other characters in the guild would be inclined to give my character a hard time if they thought he was helping &quot;evil&quot;, despite the emotes or comments made while granting that help...so my character chooses not to do anything to that could be misconstrued as &quot;aiding evil&quot; when certain members of his guild family are around.<br>
<br>
RPing true neutral is a valid option, and it sounds like you make a good attempt at it.  I found it difficult to RP true neutral while being in a good aligned guild, so I chose to RP Tuppen as neutral good.  That means having him be a bit prejudiced when it comes to the classes and races which have been defined by the creators of EQ as &quot;evil&quot;. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=mysteweave>Mysteweave</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 345<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/18/03 11:19 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3878.topic&index=37>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Sanctum Lux.....</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Actually, the poster has a point... the person, having said &quot;I will not group with evils&quot; should then have said &quot;and I will have to leave the group if you invite them&quot; rather than &quot;so they can't join group&quot;.<br>
<br>
The person wasn't prepared to live with the consequences of roleplaying - that sometimes you have to give up groups.<br>
<br>
That they were group leader means nothing in a pick up group.<br>
<br>
The person did not have the right to dictate that evils couldn't join the group unless he is supported by the majority of group members.<br>
<br>
That said, although he should not have dictated it, it would be a cold hearted group that did not see his point of view and let him stay, postponing the grouping of the two evils.<br>
<br>
All of which has precisely zero to do with the guy's guild, that I can see. =)<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I agree with Shackelton here.<br>
<br>
But its an agreement in hindsight. My guess is the player simply didn't think of it, though it might of been best if they did.<br>
<br>
Just because you've been in that group the longest, or you started the pickup group doesn't necessarily mean you should dictate it. If he was the only one in the group that didn't want to group with evils, he could of said something like: I'm sorry, this is my guild rule: guild_rule_here. I would perfer not to invite two more evils to this group -- do you mind? If you do, then I am sorry, if you want them I will need to leave the group. I will leave it up to you. <br>
<br>
However, if he didn't say something nice and polite like this, then it is up to the group to dictate how it will go, and they all could of left the group like the necro who did leave the group did. However, then there could of been a nasty fight over who actually gets to keep the spot for killing bandits -- the Group leader who started the group and 'got the spot' or the group that leaves said group leader? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> . My guess is they all wanted to stay in the primo spot and probably didn't feel like getting into a battle royalle over who got to stay at the bandit camp. Course, you could argue that said solo group leader who is left high and dry, can't hold the camp by himself would have to move on -- but then he might be here flaming the members of his group for being dipwads, and ditching him for no real good reason other than an RP one and we'd probably all be flaming you guys for making a person who dared to RP feel like crap.<br>
<br>
Oh wait, that's already happening!<br>
<br>
*sigh*<br>
